    <note type="biography">
        <p>English-born botanist, horticulturist, and author. Gardener at the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, 1845–8. In 1848, emigrated to the United States, where he worked as a gardener. Established a nursery in Germantown, Pennsylvania, <hi rend="italic">circa</hi> 1853. Editor, <hi rend="italic">Gardener’s Monthly</hi>, 1859–87; <hi rend="italic">Meehan’s Monthly</hi>, 1891–1901. Botanist on the Philadelphia state board of agriculture, 1877–1901. Elected to the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 1860; to the American Philosophical Society, 1871.</p></note>
